      "rationale": "NIH predictions were compared against FDA GCBP bench data at three operating points within the CPB envelope (2.5, 3.0, 3.5 L/min). Mean relative error was 14.2% with all predictions within the combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands. The Leverett VAD dataset was also cited as corroborating evidence; agreement at equivalent shear levels was within 18%. The assessment team accepted both comparisons as meeting Gradation 2, without noting that the Leverett dataset was collected under VAD flow conditions (6–10 L/min) outside the CPB operating range declared in the COU."
